# Feature architecture (mandatory for new features)

When designing or implementing a **feature**, use exactly this layout under `lib/<feature>/`, plus the DI files below. Do **not** add other extra files (no barrel files, helpers, or alternate folders unless the user explicitly asks).

## App and module DI (GetIt)

- **`lib/init.dart`** — exports `GetIt sl` (`GetIt.instance`) and `Future<void> configureDependencies()` for **app-wide** registrations only (e.g. `http.Client`, shared services). No feature-specific types here.
- **`lib/<feature>/<feature>_di.dart`** — `abstract final class ExpenseDi`-style name: **PascalCase feature segment + `Di`** (folder `expense` → class `ExpenseDi`, file `expense_di.dart`). `static Future<void> initialize()` registers every GetIt binding for that feature (data sources, repository impl, use cases). Use `GetIt.instance` inside the module (or resolve deps via types already registered in core or other features). Prefer constructing blocs in `BlocProvider(create: ...)` in routes, not GetIt, unless the project standardizes bloc registration.
- **`lib/main.dart`** — after `WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized()`, call in order: `await configureDependencies();` then `await <Feature>Di.initialize();` for each feature (order matters when one module depends on types registered in core or another module). **`test/`** setup that resets GetIt must repeat the same sequence after `sl.reset()`.

```text
lib/
  init.dart   # sl + configureDependencies() — core only
  <feature>/
    <feature>_di.dart   # <Feature>Di.initialize() — this feature’s GetIt registrations
    data/
      datasources/
        <feature>_remote_data_source.dart
        <feature>_local_data_source.dart
      repository/
        <feature>_repository_impl.dart
      dtos/
        <feature>_dto.dart   # json_serializable + json_annotation; mappers to domain models live here
    domain/
      repository/
        <feature>_repository.dart
      use_case/
        <one dart file per use case / piece of functionality>.dart
      model/
        <relevant models>.dart
    presentation/
      bloc/
        <feature>_bloc.dart
        <feature>_event.dart
        <feature>_state.dart
      ui/
        <feature>_screen.dart   # and/or route as needed
        widgets/
```

## Stack and layer rules

- **State:** `flutter_bloc` — UI talks only to the feature bloc (events in, states out).
- **DI:** `get_it` — core in `init.dart`; each feature’s types in that feature’s `<feature>_di.dart` inside `initialize()` (see above).
- **DTOs:** `json_serializable` + `json_annotation`; mapping **DTO ↔ domain model** belongs with the DTO (or in that DTO file), not scattered.
- **Domain models:** Plain data holders — constructors (and fields/getters) only; **no** business logic, serialization, or framework types.
- **Repository (domain):** Abstract contract in `domain/repository/`.
- **Repository impl (data):** Implements that contract; inject and call **remote** and/or **local** data sources as the feature requires.

## Data flow (strict)

One direction for actions and results:

`presentation (UI) → Bloc → UseCase → Repository → DataSource`  
and back: `DataSource → Repository → UseCase → Bloc → UI`

Do not skip layers (e.g. UI must not call repositories or data sources directly).

## Naming

Replace `<feature>` with the feature name (e.g. `auth`, `profile`). Use the same prefix for bloc, repository, DTO, and data source file names for that feature.
